WEBVTT

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.600
Everything in the future will be experiential.

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:13.000
It will be tailored to an individual user, it will be, you know,

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:15.800
tailored to the algorithm, all of these things.

00:00:15.800 --> 00:00:19.400
And so you're not really focused on a single output anymore,

00:00:19.400 --> 00:00:24.000
you're focused on an entire design system that needs to move and change and evolve.

00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:32.400
At Black Math, we start with art.

00:00:32.400 --> 00:00:36.200
Our goals are to make incredible work, our goals are to make original work.

00:00:36.200 --> 00:00:40.400
We used to make one thing, hand it off and never see it again.

00:00:40.400 --> 00:00:45.000
And now the work that we make, we are building it to be extendable,

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:47.800
we're building it to be more interactive.

00:00:51.600 --> 00:00:53.800
I don't want to see anyone stuck in a prompt box.

00:00:53.800 --> 00:00:58.600
I want a tool that will evolve with the creatives in our company.

00:00:58.600 --> 00:01:03.400
With ComfyUI you have this opportunity to build a full mind map of the project.

00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:07.400
It feels like this kind of canvas that you can make your own.

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:10.800
As a supervising technical director, I'm basically

00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:14.400
guiding our artist team through the technical weeds.

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:17.000
I think it really improves the whole efficiency

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:19.400
because it gives you a lot of possibilities.

00:01:19.400 --> 00:01:25.000
So I tend to selectively use it to rapidly explore directions

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:29.800
while also keeping the focus on strong art direction.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:32.600
You want people on your team that are about creative enablement,

00:01:32.600 --> 00:01:37.400
that are about sort of technical workflows and technical pipelines.

00:01:37.800 --> 00:01:45.000
Because we are enabling our clients to do more with our creative output.

00:01:45.800 --> 00:01:48.800
Art and design will need to be living, breathing things.

00:01:48.800 --> 00:01:54.600
And I think that interactivity is really, really interesting because it allows people to actually take part in design

00:01:54.600 --> 00:01:58.400
and kind of creates a conversation between creator and user.
